FROM CALIGULA'S TIME.

30:59.457 --> 31:03.928
I GREW UP WATCHING "I,
CLAUDIUS."
I LOVED THE BOOK.
I LOVE THE OLD TV SERIES.

31:03.995 --> 31:09.667
YOU'RE TELLING ME, A LOT OF THAT
JUST WASN'T TRUE.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: NOW, WHAT
I'M NOT DENYING IS THEY HAD SEX

31:09.734 --> 31:15.773
IN THE PALACE.
OF COURSE THEY HAD SEX.
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )
PRETTY SPECTACULARLY, OF COURSE

31:15.840 --> 31:19.510
THEY HAD SEX.
>> Cooper: (<i> LAUGHS</i> )
PRETTY SPECTACULARLY?
>> Cooper: BUT WALLACE-HADRILL

31:19.577 --> 31:24.749
DOES BELIEVE CALIGULA COULD BE
VERY IMPULSIVE AND BRUTAL, AND
HE DOESN'T RULE OUT THE
POSSIBILITY THAT HE MAY HAVE HAD

31:24.816 --> 31:30.755
A SEVERE PHYSICAL OR MENTAL
DISORDER.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: I THINK
THERE'S A SERIOUS DANGER THAT

31:30.822 --> 31:39.397
CALIGULA WAS-- WAS PATHOLOGICAL,
THAT HE ACTUALLY DIDN'T CARE
ABOUT THE HURT HE CAUSED.
>> Cooper: WALLACE-HADRILL SAYS

31:39.464 --> 31:47.405
ROBERT GRAVES' NOVELS WERE
LARGELY BASED ON STORIES
PUBLISHED AROUND 121 A.D.,
80 YEARS AFTER CALIGULA'S DEATH,

31:47.472 --> 31:54.045
BY SUETONIUS, A WELL-KNOWN
BIOGRAPHER AND ADVISER TO LATER
EMPERORS.
BUT SUETONIUS OFTEN HAD TO RELY

31:54.112 --> 31:59.284
ON SECOND-HAND STORIES AND
GOSSIP FROM MEMBERS OF THE
IMPERIAL COURT.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: THESE

31:59.350 --> 32:05.356
MEMBERS OF THE COURT, IT'S--
YOU KNOW, IT'S LIKE STAFFERS IN
THE WHITE HOUSE.
IT'S LIKE ALL THOSE LEAKY PEOPLE

32:05.423 --> 32:10.828
IN BUCKINGHAM PALACE.
WHAT ARE THESE STORIES WORTH?
HOW CAN YOU PIN THEM DOWN?
(<i> CHURCH BELLS</i> )

32:10.895 --> 32:18.169
>> Cooper: ARCHEOLOGY CAN
HELP PIN DOWN THE PAST, BUT IN A
CITY FULL OF AMAZING RUINS, NOT
MUCH DIRECTLY LINKED TO CALIGULA

32:18.236 --> 32:23.808
HAD BEEN DISCOVERED--
THAT IS, UNTIL 2006.
(<i> CONSTRUCTION</i> )
WHEN A PENSION FUND FOR ITALIAN

32:23.875 --> 32:30.748
DOCTORS CALLED ENPAM STARTED
DIGGING AN UNDERGROUND PARKING
GARAGE FOR ITS NEW OFFICE
BUILDING IN THE ESQUILINO

32:30.815 --> 32:38.356
NEIGHBORHOOD OF ROME.
IN ANCIENT TIMES, THIS WAS ONE
OF A NUMBER OF TRANQUIL GARDEN
ESTATES LOCATED ABOUT TEN

32:38.423 --> 32:45.797
MINUTES BY CARRIAGE FROM THE
BUSTLING ROMAN FORUM.
THESE RE-CREATIONS FROM ROME'S
SUPERINTENDENT OF ANTIQUITIES

32:45.863 --> 32:53.871
GIVE SOME SENSE OF THE SPRAWLING
GROUNDS AND BUILDINGS ENJOYED BY
EMPERORS AND THEIR GUESTS FOR
ABOUT FOUR CENTURIES.

32:53.938 --> 32:59.544
IT TOOK ARCHEOLOGISTS NINE YEARS
TO CAREFULLY RECOVER MORE THAN A
MILLION PIECES OF THE PAST,
WHILE AN UNDERGROUND PARKING

32:59.610 --> 33:05.650
GARAGE AND MODERN BUILDING WAS
BUILT AROUND THEM.
(<i> EXCAVATION</i> )
EVERYTHING FOUND WAS TAKEN TO A

33:05.717 --> 33:12.757
LARGE WAREHOUSE, WHERE IT WAS
CLOSELY ANALYZED, LOGGED INTO A
DATABASE, AND-- WHEN POSSIBLE--
PAINSTAKINGLY RESTORED.

33:12.824 --> 33:19.497
THE OFFICE BUILDING'S COMPLETED
NOW, AND LAST MONTH, ROME'S
NEWEST ARCHEOLOGICAL SITE, THE
NYMPHEUM MUSEUM, OPENED IN THE

33:19.564 --> 33:27.438
BASEMENT, PRESERVING SOME OF THE
EXCAVATION, AND SUGGESTING WHAT
A LUSH AND LAVISH PLACE THIS
ONCE WAS.

33:27.505 --> 33:35.413
IT CONTAINS THOUSANDS OF ITEMS,
FROM THE SECOND CENTURY B.C.
THROUGH THE FIFTH CENTURY A.D.,
LIKE THIS DRINKING GLASS THAT

33:35.480 --> 33:42.754
SOMEHOW SURVIVED LARGELY INTACT
FOR 1,900 YEARS.
MIRELLA SERLORENZI, DIRECTOR OF
EXCAVATIONS FOR THE ITALIAN

33:42.820 --> 33:48.726
MINISTRY OF CULTURE, TOOK US TO
A SMALL STAIRCASE NORMALLY
CLOSED TO THE PUBLIC, AND
BROUGHT US TO THE LEVEL OF THE

33:48.793 --> 33:57.468
GROUND DURING CALIGULA'S TIME.
AND SO, BACK THEN, IN THE FIRST
CENTURY, 2,000 YEARS AGO, THIS
WAS OUTSIDE?

33:57.535 --> 34:03.541
>> Mirella Serlorenzi
(<i> translated</i> ): IT WAS CLEARLY
A GARDEN, BECAUSE WE FOUND IN
THE LAYERS TRACES OF THE ROOTS

34:03.608 --> 34:10.648
OF THE PLANTS, AND IN THIS
PART HERE, THE STAIRCASE
CONNECTED THE VARIOUS LEVELS OF
THE GARDEN.

34:10.715 --> 34:15.386
>> Cooper: IS IT POSSIBLE TO
WALK ON IT?
>> Serlorenzi:<i> ASSOLUTAMENTE.</i>
>> Cooper: YEAH?

34:15.453 --> 34:23.394
EXCELLENT.
THIS IS WHAT SERLORENZI'S TEAM
BELIEVES THE AREA LOOKED LIKE
DURING CALIGULA'S REIGN.

34:23.461 --> 34:29.867
WE ENDED UP TALKING FOR A LONG
TIME ON THE GARDEN STEPS.
ISIT ALL RIGHT TO SIT DOWN?
>> Serlorenzi: SIT, OKAY.

34:29.934 --> 34:35.406
>> Cooper: THERE WAS SOMETHING
ABOUT TOUCHING THOSE OLD SLABS
OF MARBLE THAT MADE ANCIENT
HISTORY FEEL VERY REAL.

34:35.473 --> 34:42.480
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT WE ARE
SITTING ON THE STEPS THAT
CALIGULA MAY HAVE WALKED ON.
IT'S AMAZING.

34:42.547 --> 34:47.485
SHE TOLD US THE WATER PIPE BY
OUR FEET WAS INSTALLED BY
CALIGULA'S SUCCESSOR, HIS UNCLE
CLAUDIUS.

34:47.552 --> 34:54.826
HIS NAME IS STAMPED ON THE PIPE.
ONE OF THE MOST REMARKABLE
THINGS ABOUT CALIGULA IS THAT HE
LIVED TO BECOME EMPEROR AT ALL.

34:54.892 --> 35:00.731
THE EMPEROR BEFORE HIM, HIS
ADOPTIVE GRANDFATHER TIBERIUS,
WAS SUSPECTED OF KILLING
CALIGULA'S FATHER, MOTHER, AND

35:00.798 --> 35:07.505
TWO BROTHERS.
AND WHEN CALIGULA TURNED 19,
HE WAS SUMMONED TO LIVE WITH
TIBERIUS AT HIS PALACE ON THE

35:07.572 --> 35:15.379
ISLAND OF CAPRI.
IT SITS HIGH ON A CLIFF, AND
IT'S SAID TIBERIUS WOULD HAVE
PEOPLE WHO CROSSED HIM TOSSED

35:15.446 --> 35:22.320
ONTO THE ROCKS BELOW.
THROUGH SOME COMBINATION OF
FLATTERY AND DECEIT, CALIGULA
MANAGED TO SURVIVE HERE FOR

35:22.386 --> 35:30.228
SIX YEARS WITH THE MAN WHO MAY
HAVE KILLED MUCH OF HIS FAMILY.
HE BECAME TIBERIUS'S SUCCESSOR
IN 37 A.D.

35:30.294 --> 35:35.700
HE WAS JUST 24 YEARS OLD, AND IN
CHARGE OF AN EMPIRE.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: HE WAS IN A
VERY, VERY DIFFICULT POSITION.

35:35.766 --> 35:46.911
I LIKE THE SAYING OF TIBERIUS,
WHO SAYS, "BEING EMPEROR IS
LIKE HAVING TO HOLD A WOLF BY
THE EARS."

35:46.978 --> 35:51.782
THERE'S THIS SORT OF SAVAGE
BEAST, THAT CAN TURN ON YOU ANY
MOMENT.
>> Cooper: WHAT IS SO INSECURE

35:51.849 --> 35:59.257
ABOUT IT?
WAS IT THE SYSTEM ITSELF?
>> Wallace-Hadrill: YOU'VE GOT
THIS ENORMOUS CONCENTRATION OF

35:59.323 --> 36:06.697
POWER AND RESOURCE, WEALTH,
CONCENTRATED ON THE PALACE IN
ROME.
AND EVERYONE WANTS IN ON IT.

36:06.764 --> 36:11.802
AND THEY ARE PREPARED TO DO
ANYTHING TO SEIZE THIS POWER.
>> Cooper: BACK THEN, THE ROMAN
EMPIRE DOMINATED THE

36:11.869 --> 36:19.143
MEDITERRANEAN WORLD.
AND ITEMS FOUND IN THE GARDENS
GIVE SOME SENSE OF THE RICHES
THAT FLOWED TOWARDS ROME.

36:19.210 --> 36:24.749
RARE AND INTRICATELY-CARVED
MARBLE FROM THE FAR REACHES OF
THE EMPIRE DECORATED THE WALLS
OF THE BUILDINGS.

36:24.815 --> 36:30.221
GLASS RECOVERED AT THE SITE
APPEARS TO HAVE BEEN USED IN
VERY EARLY WINDOWS.
AND, LARGE AMOUNTS OF OYSTERS

36:30.288 --> 36:35.393
APPEAR TO HAVE BEEN SERVED AT
MEALS.
MIRELLA SERLORENZI SAYS HER
TEAM RECOVERED THE BONES OF

36:35.459 --> 36:41.165
WILD ANIMALS THAT WOULD
HAVE BEEN BROUGHT HERE FROM
FAR-AWAY LANDS.
SHE SHOWED US THE LEG OF AN

36:41.232 --> 36:47.038
OSTRICH, THE FOOT OF A LION, AND
THE TOOTH OF A BEAR.
>> Serlorenzi (<i> translated</i> ):
IT'S EVIDENT THAT WILD ANIMALS

36:47.104 --> 36:54.211
WERE HERE FOR THE ENTERTAINMENT
OF THE EMPEROR.
GAMES WERE CARRIED OUT HERE WITH
GLADIATORS, WE CAN IMAGINE, AND

36:54.278 --> 36:59.784
BATTLES WITH FEROCIOUS BEASTS.
>> Cooper: WHEN HE BECAME
EMPEROR, CALIGULA STARTED
IMPROVING ROME'S INFRASTRUCTURE.

36:59.850 --> 37:07.491
HE BEGAN WORK ON NEW AQUEDUCTS.
HE ALSO CUT TAXES.
SERLORENZI SAYS THIS COIN FOUND
IN THE GARDENS WAS MINTED AROUND

37:07.558 --> 37:15.399
39 A.D. TO REMIND ROMANS THAT
CALIGULA GOT RID OF A SALES TAX.
2,000 YEARS AGO, POLITICIANS
WERE JUST LIKE POLITICIANS

37:15.466 --> 37:21.939
TODAY?
IF THEY CUT TAXES, THEY WANTED
EVERYBODY TO KNOW ABOUT IT.
>> Serlorenzi (<i> translated</i> ):

37:22.006 --> 37:27.445
THAT'S EXACTLY RIGHT.
THE COINS ARE A FORM OF IMPERIAL
PROPAGANDA.
>> Cooper: BUT SOMETHING CHANGED

37:27.511 --> 37:35.386
AS THE YEARS PROGRESSED.
SUETONIUS SAYS CALIGULA WANTED
TO BE TREATED AS A GOD, AND
CONNECTED HIS PALACE IN THE

37:35.453 --> 37:39.190
ROMAN FORUM TO A MAJOR TEMPLE.
THAT'S THE TEMPLE OF CASTOR AND
POLLUX?
>> Paolo Carafa: EXACTLY,

37:39.256 --> 37:43.494
EXACTLY, AND THIS COLUMN HAS
BEEN STANDING THERE FOR MORE
THAN 2,000 YEARS.
>> Cooper: THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

37:43.561 --> 37:47.898
>> Carafa: THEY HAVE BEEN
CREATED IN THE YEAR SIX.
>> Cooper: PAOLO CARAFA,
PROFESSOR OF ARCHEOLOGY AT

37:47.965 --> 37:55.506
SAPIENZA UNIVERSITY OF ROME, HAS
BEEN STUDYING THE ROMAN FORUM
AREA FOR MORE THAN 35 YEARS.
SO, ACCORDING TO SUETONIUS,

37:55.573 --> 38:02.546
CALIGULA EXTENDED HIS HOUSE UP
TO THAT TEMPLE?
>> Carafa: EXACTLY.
>> Cooper: HAVE YOU FOUND

38:02.613 --> 38:09.186
EVIDENCE OF THAT?
>> Carafa: BEHIND TH TEMPLE,
RECENT EXCAVATION HAVE
IDENTIFIED FRAGMENTS OF A LARGE

38:09.253 --> 38:15.393
HOUSE, A LUXURY HOUSE.
>> Cooper: HE CAN'T SAY FOR SURE
IT WAS CALIGULA'S HOUSE, BUT HE
SAYS IT COMES FROM THAT TIME

38:15.459 --> 38:21.999
PERIOD, AND ONLY AN EMPEROR LIKE
CALIGULA WOULD HAVE DARED DO
SOMETHING SO SHOCKING.
HE WANTED THE TEMPLE TO BE THE

38:22.066 --> 38:27.038
ENTRANCE TO HIS OWN HOUSE?
>> Carafa: EXACTLY.
WHICH IS QUITE UNUSUAL.
>> Cooper: ONE OF THE THINGS

38:27.104 --> 38:33.377
"I, CLAUDIUS" SEEMS TO HAVE
GOTTEN RIGHT, WALLACE-HADRILL
TOLD US, WAS CALIGULA'S CAPACITY
FOR BOTH PHYSICAL AND MENTAL

38:33.444 --> 38:39.250
CRUELTY.
(<i> CROWD JEERS</i> )
>> Wallace-Hadrill: THERE'S NO
DOUBT THAT CALIGULA'S BRUTAL.

38:39.316 --> 38:46.123
BUT SUETONIUS SAYS HE'S NOT ONLY
BRUTAL, HE THINKS IT'S AMUSING.
HE TAKES PLEASURE IN IT.
>> Cooper: PERHAPS THE MOST

38:46.190 --> 38:51.962
TELLING ACCOUNT COMES FROM A
CONTEMPORARY OF CALIGULA'S, THE
PHILOSOPHER SENECA, WHO
DESCRIBES HOW CALIGULA INVITED A

38:52.029 --> 38:59.470
FATHER TO A FESTIVE DINNER ON
THE DAY HE HAD EXECUTED THE
MAN'S SON.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: AND AT THE

38:59.537 --> 39:09.246
DINNER, HE INSISTS THAT THE
FATHER SHOULD HAVE A JOLLY TIME.
HE PLIES HIM WITH WINE AND FOOD.
HE EVEN PLIES HIM WITH PERFUME

39:09.313 --> 39:12.750
AND A GARLAND.
>> Cooper: ON THE VERY DAY HIS
SON...
>> Wallace-Hadrill: ON THE VERY

39:12.817 --> 39:18.756
DAY.
AND SENECA SAYS, PEOPLE ASKED,
HOW ON EARTH COULD HE ENDURE TO
DO IT?

39:18.823 --> 39:27.431
AND THE ANSWER IS, HE HAD A
SECOND SON.
AND I THINK THAT ANECDOTE JUST
EVOKES THE ATMOSPHERE OF TERROR

39:27.498 --> 39:34.205
OF THE COURT OF CALIGULA.
>> Caligula: AAAAAAH!
>> Cooper: AS "I, CLAUDIUS"
SHOWED, THE END CAME IN 41 A.D.

39:34.271 --> 39:39.410
WHEN CALIGULA WAS STABBED TO
DEATH BY MEMBERS OF HIS OWN
IMPERIAL GUARD.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: HE'S KILLED

39:39.477 --> 39:47.952
BY HIS OWN GUARDSMEN, BUT THEN
THEY HAVEN'T GOT A CANDIDATE.
>> Cooper: THEY DON'T HAVE
SOMEBODY WAITING TO TAKE OVER?

39:48.018 --> 39:53.891
>> Wallace-Hadrill: THEY HAVE
NO ONE IN THE WINGS.
EXCEPT POOR OLD CLAUDIUS.
>> Cooper: DOES THAT ARGUE THE

39:53.958 --> 40:00.731
POINT THAT HE HAD TO HAVE BEEN
REALLY AWFUL IF THEY WERE SO
MOTIVATED TO JUST KILL HIM?
>> Wallace-Hadrill: YEAH, YEAH.

40:00.798 --> 40:11.509
IT'S AN ASSASSINATION BORN OF
ANGER, HUMILIATION, DISGUST.
"WE CAN'T TAKE THIS ANYMORE."
>> Cooper: LONG AFTER THE

40:11.575 --> 40:18.749
ASSASSINATION ITSELF, SOME
HISTORIANS BELIEVE, CALIGULA'S
ENEMIES ASSASSINATED HIS MEMORY
AS WELL.

40:18.816 --> 40:26.824
THERE'S A NUMBER OF CONTEMPORARY
SCHOLARS WHO HAVE ARGUED THAT
CALIGULA'S CRITICS DISTORTED HIS
MEMORY, THAT THEY HAVE FALSELY

40:26.891 --> 40:30.728
MADE HIM OUT TO BE FAR WORSE
THAN HE WAS.
>> Wallace-Hadrill: OF COURSE.
IT'S LIKE ENTERING A HALL OF

40:30.795 --> 40:36.734
MIRRORS AND, YOU KNOW, SOME OF
THEM ARE CONCAVE, AND SOME ARE
CONVEX.
AND THERE ARE NO FLAT MIRRORS.

40:36.801 --> 40:46.911
>> Cooper: BUT ISN'T THAT
TERRIFYING, THAT WHAT WE THINK
WE KNOW ABOUT HISTORY IS SO
DEPENDENT ON RUMORS, OR...

40:46.977 --> 40:54.752
>> Wallace-Hadrill: BUT I THINK
IT'S AN ENORMOUS MISTAKE TO
LOOK AT THE PAST AS A SERIES OF
SOLID ROCKS THAT, YOU KNOW, THAT

40:54.819 --> 41:02.259
WAS DEFINITELY THERE.
AND THAT WAS DEFINITELY...
IT'S-- IT'S A GREAT MORASS, A
FLOWING SEA.

41:02.326 --> 41:08.399
I THINK THAT ANCIENT HISTORY'S
VERY GOOD FOR PEOPLE,<i> BECAUSE</i>
IT'S GOT SO MUCH UNCERTAINTY IN
IT.

41:08.465 --> 41:14.438
>> Cooper: BUT WHY IS IT GOOD
THAT THERE'S A LOT OF
MISINFORMATION?
>> Wallace-Hadrill: IT'S GOOD

41:14.505 --> 41:19.410
BECAUSE THE WORLD WE LIVE IN
IS FULL OF MISINFORMATION,
AS WE HAVE LEARNED SPECTACULARLY
IN RECENT YEARS.

41:19.476 --> 41:26.383
YOU KNOW?
PEOPLE INVENT TRUTHS.
YOU HAVE TO BE SKEPTICAL.
>> Cooper: AS WE PREPARED TO

41:26.450 --> 41:31.522
LEAVE THE NYMPHEUM MUSEUM, WE
COULDN'T HELP THINKING ABOUT HOW
TIME TRAMPLES EVEN THE MIGHTIEST
OF EMPIRES, TURNING LAVISH

41:31.589 --> 41:37.127
GARDENS INTO UNDERGROUND PARKING
LOTS.
WHAT DO YOU THINK CALIGULA WOULD
THINK OF-- OF WHAT'S HAPPENED TO

41:37.194 --> 41:41.932
HIS GARDENS?
>> Serlorenzi (<i> translated</i> ):
(<i> LAUGHS</i> )
I THINK HE WOULD BE IN TOTAL

41:41.999 --> 41:48.739
DISAGREEMENT.
AND, I DON'T THINK HE WOULD BE
VERY HAPPY THAT WE ARE SITTING
ON HIS STAIRCASE.

